          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "An allocator's context, a structure of type ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "CFAllocatorContext",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", holds pointers to various function callbacks (particularly those that allocate, reallocate, and deallocate memory for an object). The context also contains a version number and the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "info",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " field for program-defined data. To obtain the value of the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "info",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " field you usually first have to get an allocator's context. ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
